def bestQuiz(l):
    # Your  code goes ehre...
    #pass 
    count=[0,0,0]
    avg=[0,0,0]
    for i in range(len(l)):
            for j in range(len(l[0])):
                  if (l[i][j]!=-1):
                        avg[j]+=l[i][j]
                        count[j]+=1
      #print(count)
      #print(avg)  
    max=0
    res=0
    for j in range(len(l[0])):
            if count[j]!=0:
                  avg[j]=avg[j]/count[j]
            else:
                  avg[j]=0
            #print(max,avg[j])      
            if max<avg[j]:
                  max=avg[j]
                  res=j
      #print (max)
    if max==0:
            return None
    else:
            return res 

def testBestQuiz():
    print('Testing bestQuiz()...', end='')
    a = [ [ 88,  80, 91 ],
	    [ 68, 100, -1 ]]
    assert(bestQuiz(a) == 2)
    a = [ [ 88,  80, 80 ],
	    [ 68, 100, 100 ]]
    assert(bestQuiz(a) == 1)
    a = [ [88, -1, -1 ],
	    [68, -1, -1 ]]
    assert(bestQuiz(a) == 0)
    a = [ [-1, -1, -1 ],
	    [-1, -1, -1 ]]
    assert(bestQuiz(a) == None)
    print('All test cases passed...!')
